results.signature: IF price trades above prior swing high (buy-side liquidity) AND then reverses back below that high THEN Bullish Liquidity Sweep = TRUE
results.source_quote: Price expanded to the higher to take out buy stops, why? Because they (the Informed Money), will want to sell at a higher price, take the Liquidity and cover their long positions that they opened to run the price higher.

results.signature: IF price trades below prior swing low (sell-side liquidity) AND then reverses back above that low THEN Bearish Liquidity Sweep = TRUE
results.source_quote: What retail sees as a 'double bottom' area as strong support, what we see is all the sell stops resting below (retail stop losses) – that’s our target and a magnet where the price will be drawn to.

results.signature: IF prior structure = bullish (HH/HL) AND price breaks below most recent swing low with displacement THEN MSS = Bearish
results.source_quote: When we see market making higher highs & higher lows after already running the sell-side liquidity, we can’t reasonably expect for price to drop all the way down below the main low to take those stops out.

results.signature: IF prior structure = bearish (LL/LH) AND price breaks above most recent swing high with displacement THEN MSS = Bullish
results.source_quote: When we know what the Higher TF orderflow is we wait for retracements to ride the direction towards the Higher TF draw on Liquidity.

results.signature: IF swing point broken (sweep) BUT no displacement follows THEN MSS = INVALID
results.source_quote: IMPORTANT: when price runs a liquidity pool we want to see a strong expansion to the opposite direction right away, if price is not in a rush to leave the liquidity pool that’s the first sign that price is NOT ready to go.

results.signature: IF price move creates FVG AND move has significant range THEN Displacement = TRUE
results.source_quote: Notice how aggressively price moves away from that area, that’s the clearest & most obvious sign that the 'Smart Money' is involved – price has to run the stops and quickly move away from that area.

results.signature: IF price move has NO FVG OR move has small range THEN Displacement = FALSE
results.source_quote: if price is not in a rush to leave the liquidity pool that’s the first sign that price is NOT ready to go.
